CHISHOLM, Appellant, v. PROUT, Respondent. (Supreme Court, General Term, First Department. February 16, 1894.) Action by Alexander Chisholm against Moses P. Prout.

Argued before VAN BRUNT, P. J., and O’BRIEN and FOLLETT, JJ..

E. G. Perkins, for appellant. G'. H. Crawford, for respondent.

No opinion. Order affirmed, with $10 costs and disbursements.
